Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.69,0:00:10.10,Italics,Goblin lord,0,0,0,,How did it come to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.16,0:00:15.50,Italics,GL,0,0,0,,That horde is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.50,0:00:18.07,Italics,GL,0,0,0,,There's no point in staying \Nnow that they've been halted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.63,0:00:20.65,Italics,GL,0,0,0,,I need only keep myself alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.65,0:00:24.37,Italics,GL,0,0,0,,I'll go back to my nest, reproduce \Nusing the prisoners I have there,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.37,0:00:25.99,Italics,GL,0,0,0,,and try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.66,0:00:31.59,Italics,GL,0,0,0,,I failed this time, but as long as I'm alive,\Nthere will always be a next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.59,0:00:33.58,Italics,GL,0,0,0,,I'll make it work next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.17,0:00:36.02,Italics,Gl,0,0,0,,Next time, for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.99,0:00:45.39,Main,Goblin Slayer,0,0,0,,I knew that was what you'd think.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.14,0:00:54.79,Main,gS,0,0,0,,You fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.34,0:00:57.65,Main,GS,0,0,0,,That army was just a decoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.26,0:01:07.07,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Your home is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.47,0:02:52.60,Ep_Title,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(272,1)}The Fate of an Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.78,0:03:39.77,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I'm not used to fighting them face-to-face.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.27,0:04:09.43,Main,Greenhorn warrior,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.43,0:04:10.28,Main,Apprentice cleric,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.28,0:04:20.47,Main,GW,0,0,0,,I did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.02,0:04:26.30,Main,Dwarf Shaman,0,0,0,,Looks like most of them \Nhave been taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.30,0:04:27.48,Main,High elf archer,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.69,0:04:32.35,Main,hEA,0,0,0,,Still, the possibility of all these goblins \Nattacking the town gives me chills.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.35,0:04:36.37,Main,DS,0,0,0,,I think we've become pretty \Nknowledgeable about goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.94,0:04:39.15,Main,DS,0,0,0,,We've got a great teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.15,0:04:41.33,Main,HEA,0,0,0,,I'd rather not hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.33,0:04:44.50,Main,HEA,0,0,0,,This isn't how adventures are supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.95,0:04:50.97,Main,Lizardman Priest,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.79,0:04:57.23,Main,Spearman,0,0,0,,Take that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.33,0:05:07.48,Italics,Heavy swordsman,0,0,0,,He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.03,0:05:10.23,Italics,HS,0,0,0,,used to fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.49,0:05:15.83,Main,Female knight,0,0,0,,I'll draw him to me and give you an opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.31,0:05:17.37,Main,Female knight,0,0,0,,You take him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.34,0:05:20.41,Main,HS,0,0,0,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:25.46,Main,HS,0,0,0,,You're mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.11,0:05:45.35,Main,Young Scout,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.75,0:05:48.42,Main,Female knight,0,0,0,,Looks like I saved your life again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.42,0:05:51.07,Main,HS,0,0,0,,Yeah. You deserve its head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.74,0:05:54.39,Main,FK,0,0,0,,You're thanking me with the goblin's head?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:05:56.35,Main,HS,0,0,0,,You don't want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.35,0:05:58.18,Main,FK,0,0,0,,No, I'll take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:01.73,Main,HS,0,0,0,,Hey, you want some help?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.49,0:06:04.33,Main,SP,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.02,0:06:08.82,Main,Light warrior,0,0,0,,Is he going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.17,0:06:11.21,Main,Sp,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.08,0:06:33.19,Main,Sp,0,0,0,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.12,0:07:02.15,Main,Cow girl,0,0,0,,Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.86,0:07:03.89,Main,Uncle,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:08.14,Main,Cg,0,0,0,,Do you remember what you \Nsaid about him before?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.51,0:07:12.47,Main,Uncle,0,0,0,,About him not being all there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.87,0:07:14.90,Main,CG,0,0,0,,Do you still think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.90,0:07:15.86,Main,Uncle,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.29,0:07:18.28,Main,Uncle,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.96,0:07:20.16,Main,Cg,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.77,0:08:35.15,Main,P,0,0,0,,O merciful Earth Mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.44,0:08:39.94,Main,P,0,0,0,,please protect us, the weak, \Nwith the powers of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.26,0:08:43.28,Main,P,0,0,0,,Protection!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.84,0:09:17.35,Main,GL,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.35,0:09:21.87,Main,GL,0,0,0,,I'll... never do anything like this again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.87,0:09:24.42,Main,GL,0,0,0,,I-I'll go back to the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.42,0:09:27.57,Main,GL,0,0,0,,and live peacefully...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.63,0:09:54.93,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Like hell that's going to work...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.42,0:10:01.02,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Lord? Preposterous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.90,0:10:04.61,Main,GS,0,0,0,,You're just a goblin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.89,0:10:07.57,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Just a filthy little goblin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.31,0:10:12.93,Main,GS,0,0,0,,And I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.34,0:10:17.14,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Goblin Slayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.96,0:10:22.26,Main,GS,0,0,0,,That's one goblin head...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.26,0:10:23.84,Main,Priestess,0,0,0,,Goblin Slayer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.67,0:10:34.46,Flashback,GS,0,0,0,,I'll act as the bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.46,0:10:36.60,Flashback,GS,0,0,0,,Use Protection to render the lord immobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.90,0:10:38.62,Flashback,P,0,0,0,,Protection?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.62,0:10:42.33,Flashback,GS,0,0,0,,Yes. Use two and try to trap \Nhim from the front and back...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.33,0:10:46.28,Flashback,GS,0,0,0,,No, actually, use three and \Ncreate a cage to trap him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.28,0:10:47.66,Flashback,P,0,0,0,,Three?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:49.17,Flashback,GS,0,0,0,,Just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:53.92,Main,P,0,0,0,,O merciful Earth Mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.27,0:10:57.50,Main,P,0,0,0,,please place your gentle hand \Nupon this being's wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.14,0:10:59.06,Main,P,0,0,0,,Heal!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.14,0:11:05.31,Main,P,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.81,0:11:08.55,Main,P,0,0,0,,I ended up only using two Protections.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:11.22,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.62,0:11:13.30,Main,P,0,0,0,,Please don't push yourself so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:17.02,Main,GS,0,0,0,,It's not that I think I can win \Njust by pushing myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.02,0:11:18.31,Main,P,0,0,0,,Goblin Slayer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.54,0:11:22.74,Main,P,0,0,0,,You said you wouldn't \Npush yourself anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.39,0:11:28.35,Main,P,0,0,0,,Goblin Slayer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.59,0:11:35.23,Main,P,0,0,0,,Please try to think things \Nthrough a little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.23,0:11:36.24,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.99,0:11:40.21,Main,GS,0,0,0,,It's because... I trusted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.19,0:11:45.38,Main,P,0,0,0,,You truly are...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.94,0:11:47.96,Main,P,0,0,0,,such a helpless person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.11,0:12:31.18,Main,GS,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.96,0:12:41.85,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.49,0:12:44.63,Main,CG,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.40,0:12:47.96,Main,Hero,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.64,0:12:51.99,Main,Sage,0,0,0,,Calm down, please. \NYou're going to trip and fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.39,0:12:54.61,Main,Hero,0,0,0,,Heck no, I'm not gonna fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.83,0:12:59.12,Main,Hero,0,0,0,,Hurry up! The festival's \Ngonna start without us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.48,0:13:03.95,Main,Sage,0,0,0,,I still don't see why we had to leave so early...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.95,0:13:07.23,Main,Swordmaster,0,0,0,,We're going there to crush \Nthe evil sect's plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.23,0:13:10.63,Main,SM,0,0,0,,We're still pretty far from the \Ntown and the start of the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:12.55,Main,Sage,0,0,0,,Speaking of remnants of evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.55,0:13:16.11,Main,Sage,0,0,0,,apparently goblins appeared around here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.11,0:13:20.02,Main,SM,0,0,0,,Goblins? They're just underlings, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:22.77,Main,Hero,0,0,0,,Wow, you don't know, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.77,0:13:26.16,Main,Hero,0,0,0,,Goblins can be pretty scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:30.15,Main,Sage,0,0,0,,Well, I heard there's a Goblin Slayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.15,0:13:31.97,Main,Sage,0,0,0,,I think everything will be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.97,0:13:33.24,Main,SM,0,0,0,,A Goblin Slayer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.70,0:13:39.24,Main,Hero,0,0,0,,So the reason I'm able to attend the \Nfestival is thanks to whoever that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.89,0:13:44.92,Main,Hero,0,0,0,,It would sort of suck if the town was \Ndestroyed right after we saved the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.28,0:13:48.88,Main,HEA,0,0,0,,To our fallen comrades,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:50.90,Main,Hea,0,0,0,,our victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.90,0:13:53.74,Main,Hea,0,0,0,,the farm, the town, adventurers...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:54.95,Main,Hea,0,0,0,,And of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.95,0:13:58.87,Main,Hea,0,0,0,,that weirdo over there who never \Ntalks about anything but goblins!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.29,0:14:00.56,Main,HEA,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.90,0:14:02.93,Main,All,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.46,0:14:11.68,Main,Adventurer,0,0,0,,Hey, over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.68,0:14:12.40,Main,Guild girl,0,0,0,,You got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.94,0:14:14.34,Main,Witch,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.35,0:14:14.34,Main,SP,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.99,0:14:19.57,Main,FK,0,0,0,,What?! But it was a champion!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.06,0:14:22.61,Main,FK,0,0,0,,Even a champion's only \Nworth single gold coin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.61,0:14:23.78,Main,GG,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.78,0:14:28.49,Main,GG,0,0,0,,The deal was a gold coin \Nfor each goblin, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.80,0:14:31.56,Main,FK,0,0,0,,Couldn't you add a special reward?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.56,0:14:32.87,Main,Manager,0,0,0,,Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.87,0:14:35.59,Main,Manager,0,0,0,,Rewarding gold coins to all \Nof you {\i1}is{\i0} the special reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.95,0:14:39.43,Main,GG,0,0,0,,Not to mention the lord \Nthat Goblin Slayer defeated
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.97,0:14:42.24,Main,GG,0,0,0,,is also only worth one gold coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.00,0:14:53.44,Main,CG,0,0,0,,She must be exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.01,0:14:57.65,Main,GG,0,0,0,,She's a girl, so don't make \Nher push herself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.96,0:14:58.78,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:02.49,Main,CG,0,0,0,,You're being nice. Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.75,0:15:05.13,Main,GS,0,0,0,,No. I'm the same as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.45,0:15:06.62,Main,CG,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.07,0:15:10.77,Main,Female warrior,0,0,0,,Woohoo! I'm worth five gold coins tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.77,0:15:12.38,Main,Female warrior,0,0,0,,Keep the food and drink comin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:16.58,Main,CG,0,0,0,,Adventurers, we've brought more alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.58,0:15:17.76,Main,SP,0,0,0,,Hell yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:19.62,Main,Cg,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.35,0:15:21.37,Main,GS,0,0,0,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.05,0:15:23.51,Main,CG,0,0,0,,For saving us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.33,0:15:26.06,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.80,0:15:28.76,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I'm still...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.85,0:15:33.99,Main,Gs,0,0,0,,I'm still not completely sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.21,0:15:37.53,Main,GS,0,0,0,,But I'm getting a clearer idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.03,0:15:45.12,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I think I want to be an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.12,0:15:48.58,Main,CG,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.10,0:15:51.23,Main,CG,0,0,0,,I'm sure you'll be able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.68,0:15:52.74,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.74,0:15:54.61,Main,CG,0,0,0,,Yup, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:03.26,Main,P,0,0,0,,Huh?! D-Did I fall asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.77,0:16:06.79,Main,CG,0,0,0,,You worked so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.79,0:16:10.12,Main,P,0,0,0,,Huh? Um... I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.56,0:16:11.96,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.91,0:16:20.79,Main,CG,0,0,0,,I'm going to go thank everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.34,0:16:23.52,Main,CG,0,0,0,,Have a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.18,0:16:27.56,Main,P,0,0,0,,Um... What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:30.36,Main,GS,0,0,0,,You're the one who finished off the lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.36,0:16:31.46,Main,P,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.98,0:16:36.42,Main,P,0,0,0,,Are you sure that's okay, Goblin Slayer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.42,0:16:37.51,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:39.67,Main,P,0,0,0,,I-I mean, the money...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.20,0:16:44.30,Main,GS,0,0,0,,There's no problem. I paid just \Nlike we'd originally negotiated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.56,0:16:47.66,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I bought them a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.25,0:16:54.03,Main,P,0,0,0,,Goblin Slayer...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.43,0:16:55.27,Main,GS,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.88,0:16:59.41,Main,P,0,0,0,,Why didn't you... um...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.41,0:17:01.77,Main,P,0,0,0,,post a quest for everyone sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.20,0:17:04.57,Main,P,0,0,0,,You didn't have to go about it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.57,0:17:09.29,Main,P,0,0,0,,Couldn't you have just posted a quest?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.94,0:17:12.84,Main,P,0,0,0,,Of course, if you didn't want to, \Nthat's totally fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.41,0:17:15.16,Main,GS,0,0,0,,It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:19.25,Main,GS,0,0,0,,No one came when it happened to my village.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.11,0:17:22.27,Main,GS,0,0,0,,The same thing might've happened this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.97,0:17:26.79,Main,GS,0,0,0,,There were no guarantees. \NI had to trust in luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.57,0:17:29.11,Main,GS,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.58,0:17:32.27,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Apparently, I'm a weirdo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.09,0:17:36.80,Main,P,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.80,0:17:40.44,Main,P,0,0,0,,If you asked me for help, \NI would be happy to!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.79,0:17:42.18,Main,P,0,0,0,,It's not just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.18,0:17:45.28,Main,P,0,0,0,,I think all the adventurers in \Nthis town would say the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.28,0:17:48.07,Main,P,0,0,0,,This time, next time, \Nand every time after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.07,0:17:50.74,Main,P,0,0,0,,If you asked for help,\N we'd always be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.68,0:17:52.59,Main,P,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.45,0:17:56.01,Main,P,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.38,0:17:57.08,Main,P,0,0,0,,at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.86,0:17:59.79,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.11,0:18:02.48,Main,P,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.92,0:18:20.83,Main,P,0,0,0,,Hey, Goblin Slayer...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.83,0:18:24.88,Main,P,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I ask for a reward, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.88,0:18:25.95,Main,GS,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.36,0:18:32.10,Main,P,0,0,0,,Please take off your helmet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.18,0:18:34.87,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.46,0:18:39.98,Main,P,0,0,0,,I kept my eyes closed that other time \Nbecause I was so embarrassed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.39,0:19:03.61,Main,P,0,0,0,,I think you look a lot cooler this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.00,0:19:05.91,Main,GS,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.13,0:19:08.11,Main,HEA,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.38,0:19:11.46,Main,HEA,0,0,0,,Orcbolg took his helmet off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.46,0:19:14.37,Main,HEA,0,0,0,,No fair! I'd never seen his \Nface before, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.08,0:19:16.20,Main,SP,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.99,0:19:24.37,Main,GG,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness! This is a rare moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.37,0:19:26.38,Main,CG,0,0,0,,Huh? Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.90,0:19:28.85,Main,CG,0,0,0,,I guess it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.85,0:19:32.15,Main,CG,0,0,0,,The only time he willingly \Ntakes off his helmet
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.15,0:19:34.35,Main,CG,0,0,0,,is when it breaks or when he sleeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:36.35,Main,LP,0,0,0,,Hey... Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:38.40,Main,LP,0,0,0,,Ah, now this is the face of a warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.39,0:19:43.37,Main,DS,0,0,0,,You have excellent features \Nindeed, Beard-cutter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.37,0:19:45.94,Main,HEA,0,0,0,,Hey! Get outta the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.19,0:19:52.84,Main,W,0,0,0,,As I... figured... He's quite... \Nhandsome... isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.84,0:19:55.49,Main,SP,0,0,0,,Huh... I could swear I've seen \Nhim somewhere before...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.49,0:19:57.41,Main,SP,0,0,0,,Damn it! This pisses me off for some reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:20:00.86,Main,Guy A,0,0,0,,Hey, it's Goblin Slayer's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.86,0:20:03.26,Main,Guy A,0,0,0,,Bring out the betting pool!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.26,0:20:06.67,Main,Guy B,0,0,0,,Damn it! I was betting that he was a woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.67,0:20:08.96,Main,Girl A,0,0,0,,I totally thought he was a goblin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.96,0:20:11.97,Main,Guy C,0,0,0,,Hey! Did anyone guess correctly?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.97,0:20:13.64,Main,Guy C,0,0,0,,If you did, buy us all a round!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.94,0:20:22.56,Main,P,0,0,0,,If you asked for help, \Nwe'd always be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.48,0:20:26.49,Main,P,0,0,0,,So... It has nothing to do with luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.49,0:20:27.32,Main,P,0,0,0,,at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.59,0:20:30.63,Main,Gs,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.47,0:20:33.82,Main,GS,0,0,0,,I hope that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:22.87,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,This adventurer was an ordinary young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.37,0:22:26.69,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,He was a man you could find anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.07,0:22:31.20,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,The gods favored him as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.20,0:22:34.19,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,but they didn't expect \Nanything special from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.70,0:22:39.09,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,For he was just another pawn \Nthey could find anywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.71,0:22:44.36,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,However, that adventurer was \Nslightly different from the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.01,0:22:49.33,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,He was always concocting strategies, \Nthinking, taking action,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.33,0:22:53.19,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,training, using his wits, and being thorough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.94,0:22:58.32,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,He never let the gods roll the dice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.86,0:23:02.17,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,And then, one day,\N the gods finally realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.64,0:23:05.79,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,He would probably never save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.79,0:23:08.58,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,He would probably never change anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.30,0:23:13.41,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,For he was just another pawn \Nthey could find anywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.25,0:23:19.16,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,But he would never let \Nthe gods roll the dice.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.84,0:23:23.45,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,And that's exactly why \Neven the gods don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.66,0:23:26.12,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,the fate of this particular adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.00,0:23:31.35,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,His battle continues today,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.83,0:23:34.02,Narration,Nar,0,0,0,,somewhere out there.
